column3: Apologies, I hadn't realised that commit had snuck in, it's not something I've edited and assume it's come from something going wrong with the merge to my fork. I'm actually unsure how and the best way to squash this one, any advice on the best process?\n\nThanks!
Please also set a more detailed PR and commit title.
I admit that it's pretty hard to describe this particular tooltip message, but "hide button tool tip" implies that the commit *itself* is hiding something.
Just realised which title you are referring to, I'll get this updated later today.\nThanks
